15:
In a king's smile there is life;
\q2 when he is happy, he is like the cloud that brings the spring rain.
\q1

22:
When you understand, it is as if you have found a fountain of life within you; 
\q2 but fools find their punishment when their foolishness comes back to them. 
\q1

23:
From deep within him, the wise person speaks from the insight he has learned; 
\q2 and so when he speaks he has the power to pursuade others.
\q1

32:
The one who is slow to get angry is stronger than a warrior;
\q2 the one who is self-controlled is mightier than one who conquers a city by force. 
\q1
